column5: Keeping with Chris's theme and the fact that I never post pictures and just figured out how to get them from my phone to photoshop.  I figure its a slow time of year and I may as well put a few pics up looking forward to a new season about to start.  A Monday night after work.             Other days            Where we got some...pretty big water , we traveled a lot    Late season for eyes and got a surprise.     Wishing everybody a great upcoming season
Now that's my kind of fishing, and your a Crocs guy as well!
Man, those pics are getting me amped. That is a sweet live well you have.
Ummm..no on the crocs, thats the guy I was fishing with that evening..  Also please note the size of the fish, they were all caught in a no size limit area
Well, crocs are awesome, that is all.
Well, crocs are awesome, that is all.  i got crocs for christmas and am sooooo excited to use them in the boat...so functional and comfy!
We're getting there...I can kinda see my boat poking out from under the snow in the yard now...oh wait, nothing above zero for the next week, maybe next month

i got crocs for christmas and am sooooo excited to use them in the boat...so functional and comfy!  I mentioned getting a pair to the wife....she said she would leave me if I did...so....  And thats my buddys livewell, being replaced with a new 621 ranger next month
Come down and visit. Lots of water opening up here.
beauty walleyes for sure, I miss a good fish fry !!!
Nice fish!  Can't wait for some open water laker jigging!
Come down and visit. Lots of water opening up here. I'm going out with Castellano on the bar early April   That will be the start of my open water season!
Good choice, you'll have a riot with Paul.
I'm going out with Castellano on the bar early April   That will be the start of my open water season!  envious...dude is a beast
Good to see! Keep the photos/ reports coming Dara, now that you've got photobucket figured out.
